message.content:
Norway has compulsory military service for both men and women, although the country mainly recruits volunteers to serve in its armed forces. Everyone who is physically fit and aged 19-44 years must complete duty during their lifetime, whether in full-time or part-time service.

The actual length of compulsory military service varies depending on several factors such as one's role, specialization area, branch of the military etc. The typical duration of full-time basic training for enlisted troops usually ranges from 6-12 months with possible additional supplementary courses that may extend it up to two years.

After completing their initial mandatory service period, citizens can choose between entering reserve forces or signing up as a regular professional soldier within specific branches like Army Rangers (typically known as Jegertruppen), special forces (FSK/HJK) among others with longer commitments demanding increased monthly salaries.
